#: ../../right_sidebar/colors_view.rst:70
msgid "How To Use an Histogram"
msgstr "Hoe gebruikt u een histogram"

#: ../../right_sidebar/colors_view.rst:72
msgid ""
"Histograms are a graphical means to assess the accuracy of an image shown"
" on the screen. The graph represents the 3 regions of the photograph"
" brightness:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../right_sidebar/colors_view.rst:74
msgid ": the shadows-tone on the left."
msgstr ""

#: ../../right_sidebar/colors_view.rst:76
msgid ": the middle-tone in the middle."
msgstr ""

#: ../../right_sidebar/colors_view.rst:78
msgid ": the highlights-tone on the right."
msgstr ""

#: ../../right_sidebar/colors_view.rst:82
msgid ""
"The distribution of the graph, where the spikes and bulges are clustered,"
" indicates whether the image is too dark, too bright, or well-balanced."
msgstr ""

#: ../../right_sidebar/colors_view.rst:84
msgid ""
"With an under exposed photograph, the histogram will have a distribution"
" of brightness that tends to be mostly on the left of the graph."
msgstr ""

#: ../../right_sidebar/colors_view.rst:88
msgid ""
"With an over exposed photograph, the histogram will have the bulge"
" showing the brightness distributed mostly towards the right of the graph."
msgstr ""

#: ../../right_sidebar/colors_view.rst:92
msgid ""
"With a correctly exposed photograph, the histogram will have a"
" distribution of brightness that will be most prominent near the center"
" part of the graph."
msgstr ""

#: ../../right_sidebar/colors_view.rst:96
msgid ""
"Not all photographs have to exhibit this bulge in the center part of"
" their histogram. Much depends on the subject of the photograph. In some"
" cases, it might be appropriate for the histogram to show a peak at one"
" end or the other, or both."
msgstr ""

#: ../../right_sidebar/colors_view.rst:98
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The histogram is a reliable way of deciding whether or not a photograph"
" is correctly exposed. Should the histogram show an over or under"
" exposure, an Exposure Correction Tool should be used to fix the"
" photograph."
msgstr ""
"Het histogram is een betrouwbare manier om te beslissen of een foto wel"
" of "
"niet goed is belicht. Als het histogram een onder- of overbelichting "
"aantoont dan kunt u een <link linkend=\"editor-color-exposure"
"\">Belichtingscorrectie </link> gebruiken voor correctie van de foto."

